<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  My take on EQ</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
EQ... undisputedly a fun and enjoyable game, and a great way to spend that spare or 'inbetween' time during the day. All the time I'd spend watching tv or getting into trouble I now spend trolling messageboards and playing EQ. I've met many good people, and have done many amazing things that I could only dream about doing. EQ is a fantasy world full of interesting and diverse people. It's the game that makes the world, but the people that make the game. This is EQ's success. Their motto is, &quot;You're in our world now...&quot; and that's true. But just putting me in their world wouldn't be much of a game without all the amazing people, guilds, events, and raids. I enjoy every bit of it. If I didn't enjoy it, I wouldn't play. I have nothing really to complain about with EQ. EQ is what it is, and I knock on wood everyday that in the summer of 00 I went to EB and chose it over AC and UO when I was looking for a long term adventure. I found exactly what I was looking for, and it's been a great ride. When will this ride end? I don't know... do I want it to end? Nope. If something better comes along will I get it? Maybe... If I get something better will I scrap EQ? Hell no...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Poor in game antics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
The obsession that Everquest creates in us sometimes leads a select few of us to do things that are not moral, ethical, or 'nice'. This can be seen in RL too. Behind those polygon models are humans, real honest to goodness humans who are falable in every way that anyone else is. People break the law everyday, abuse each other, backstab each other, quarrel, lie, cheat, steal, KILL, and at the very least manage to tick each other off. This is normal human behavior, as sad as I am to admit it... The only thing that can be done about it is to let others know of bad deeds done, and try to lead by example. If someone does something bad to you, don't retaliate by stooping to their level. Be the bigger person, be uber, have the balls and control to be good and honest. Sure, you can sit back and say, &quot;It's only a game, I'm going to ninja loot this l33t item and then go stomp on some newbie for not knowing the game well enough.&quot; But if you have that attitude then you're missing the point, and I'm not going to waste my time explaining it to you. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Complainers about EQ</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
For those who can sit back and say that EQ has a poor design, it sucks, the expansions are worthless, and that it's graphics are the worst on the market, all I can do is laugh at that. Nothing personal, but all you have to do is look at obvious facts. First off, EQ has over 300,000 subscribers. No other online game boasts numbers like that... Asheron's Call has less than half that many players (last time I checked). Second off, look how many people play endless DAYS (not hours, days) in order to either level up one or more characters or to work on getting valuable and helpful items. But, if that's not good enough for you, look at how many people will spend DAYS of their lives to help other people do just that. EQ's graphics are far superior to that of any other MMORPG on the market right now (although that may change soon) and has been so for 2 years running.  [edit] I forgot to finish this thought! LOL!! Anyway, if you think that camping sucks, quests are retarded, and that everyone should have a fungi tunic, epic, and phat lewtz at level 1 then you've got a problem. I would be just as happy playing this game with NO gear at all. It's not about gear, and if you think it is then YOU have a problem. Should everyone in RL have a personal jet, mansion, the newest $200 nike sneakers, a wardrobe of $5,000 suits, and season tickets to the Lakers? People have a problem today with material worries. It's always me me me, mine mine mine, and if I don't have something I don't need but I still want I'm going to whine about it. RL nor EQ is about material possessions, and if it is then once again, you've missed the point entirely.[/edit]</font><P><CENTER><A HREF="http://elementsofpower.20m.com" TARGET="_top"><IMG SRC="http://students.hamilton.edu/2002/bschulte/eqpics/newestsig.gif" WIDTH=320 HEIGHT=110 X-CLARIS-USEIMAGEWIDTH X-CLARIS-USEIMAGEHEIGHT BORDER=0 ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER><P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubicrius.show