<br>
I hold my tongue when trying to complin about EQ cause hello I've been playing it for well over a year now, others nearing 3 years. It's easy to point out flaws in a game this size, but for me personally there are an extraordinary number of things in EQ which are great. I agree Verant gets heavy handed in response to player tactics evolving further than Verant intended, but in my mind it has never stopped players/guilds from adapting to the new ways. Uber mobs still are dropping after the Cleric breastplate nerfs and so forth to name one example. *sidenote: didn't Furor threaten to quit around that time also* <br>
<br>
I personally like the fact that Verant has to patch cause the users of their products are alot smarter than they thought and abuse their product/mobs. Realistically, how boring would the game be now if they had stuck to their original plans without developing the Planes, Kunark, Velious and so forth. Many of us would have quit awhile ago. So I have to cut Verant slack on that one cause the customers always have a thirst for new products, and if they hastingly put stuff in game that doesn't work as it should I can slap them on the wrist and let them try to fix it. I think most of us take this gameworld for granted like things we may take for granted in RL. Not understanding game programming I'm still sure it tooks lots of manpower and hours to get to the point we are at. *hey Absor, gimme back my keyboard* Man, I must be drunk taking up for Verant like this. At this point I'm not sure if Verant has the resources to try some of their ideas before putting them into game but I guess their rationale is we have 300K people who we can try this on, and if we screw up oh well, a patchin' we shall go.<br>
<br>
To sum things up, I probably give my overall gaming experience a B- so far. Obviously they have provided a great game for me to get lost in, but they still need to strive to be more efficient in their quality and delivery.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulieah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lieah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=70896971&img=5 BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>714</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/7/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>6:04:47 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My take</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I'll start off by saying I still love this game else I wouldn't have been playing it for over 2 years.  Its not the game I like though its the good people I meet, though I do meet some really bad ones I think that just applies everywhere you go in life. <br>
<br>
This guy has it all wrong and I'll tell ya why.  His whole reason for his not liking EQ is because of kill stealing.  Kill stealing doesn't even come close to the real problem issues in this game.  I was talking to Trystwich and several others about this last night.  The problem with the game doesn't start till 51.  There are two big huge things wrong with the game that could easily be fixed if they'd pull their heads far enough out of their asses. <br>
<br>
#1. Apparently Verant has it in thier heads that classes are somehow balanced.  Well they are in no way anywhere near balanced, AT ALL.  If classes were balanced you wouldn't REQUIRE an Enchanter, Cleric, and Evacer for everwhere you go but Karnor's Castle post 50.  A necro would actually have some use after 51 besides summoning corpses and pumping mana. A group of 6 warriors should be able to do the same damage, perhaps with a small amount of downtime as a &quot;balanced&quot; group of a cleric chanter evacer 2 tanks and a wizard type.  Warriors IMO should have twice the HP/AC they do currently.  As it stands right now Warriors have a mere 300hp more than a Paladin or SK.  How is this an advantage over having spells??? 300hp disappear in one round sometimes.  I have 300 hp less than a Paladin or SK as a Ranger, and almost as much AC.  <br>
<br>
While I admit the game should be somewhat difficult after 50, but not so time consuming as to sit for 3 hrs pulling your hair out trying to find that REQUIRED chanter when you have a good balanced group of 5 ready to go, only to have them all get impatient leave when you finally get one.  It would probably work out better if every one of those 5 people worked to find one but some people are too lazy to bother and expect someone else to do all the work for them. Thats another thing I hate, lazy people that complain about not finding groups, sitting around LFG when they could be WORKING with others to form one.<br>
<br>
#2. World size vs # of portals.  This is probably the #1 cause of the fantastic time sink in this game.   The problem may not be finding the people you need to hunt a certain dungeon.  The problem is actually getting them all in one spot w/o going through all kinds of hell.  One portal in Kunark just DOESN'T CUT IT.   Sorry 3 more bind spots wont make up for it Verant.  For instance, I had a group of 5 ready to go into Howling Stones yesterday but we ran into a snag, our Cleric was stuck way the hell over in Trakanon by Seb, and of course the only way to get there is to port to DL, run all the way to Karnor and Evacuate to EJ, then run all the way to Sebillis and get the person, port to DL run all the way to OT from there or port from Karnors to Skyfire (same distance).  What kind of sick minded idea did Verant have here? Why not just make a portal spell to EJ and Skyfire?  I have no idea why they did this and my only conclusion could be that they have never played the game before, either that or they are some pretty sick and sadistic jerks.  Do they expect us to spend one day rounding people to one spot, camp for the night and start the next day?  I mean what the hell? It doesn't work that way.<br>
<br>
Well, another view is that the 51+ game was intended for people with at least 12 hrs of playtime per day on their hands.  Its obvious.  I sure hope the next game takes these things into consideration.<br>
<br>
This guy in the review has no idea.</font><P><center><a href="http://www.silentsentinels.com"><img src="http://www.vanitey.com/profile2sig.jpg" border=0 align=bottom></a></center><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufayenae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fayenae</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>273</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5/7/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>8:06:06 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Community Supporter</FONT><BR></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My take</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Lieah, I read it 3 times.<br>
